The ELO Rating Calculation Alghoritm

\[ \begin{array}{lll} r_{i} & \leftarrow & r_i + \kappa (s_{i,j} - \mu_{i,j}) \\ r_j & \leftarrow & r_j + \kappa (s_{j,i} - \mu_{j,i}) \end{array} \] with:

  • actual result of match: \(s_{i,j}\) (a number in [0,1] )
  • predicted result: \[ \begin{array}{lll} \mu_{i,j} & = & \frac{1}{1 + 10^{-(r_i - r_j) / \zeta}} = \frac{10^{r_i / \zeta}}{10^{r_i / \zeta} + 10^{r_j / \zeta}} \\\\ \end{array} \]
  • actual score of a player: \(r_i\)
  • a learing rate k

My Choices

  • Winner goes always in White, Loser goes always in Black => score will be always be a numbers in (0.5,1]
  • given n winners and m losers, I will have
    • m/n lines where White=winner, Black=loser, Score=1
    • (eventually) one line with White=winner, Black=loser and \[Score=\frac{rest(\frac{m}{n})}{n} * 0.5 + 0.5\]
  • (Instead of character names, I should use IDs)
